criteria.driver_alignment:
IMPLEMENT — built and ran three DCF scenarios (downside, base, upside) and produced quantified enterprise values; 
VALIDATE — performed sensitivity checks (terminal weight, implied multiples) and explicitly tested WACC sensitivity; 
REPRESENT — framed the analysis within the driver framework and a three-prong valuation approach.

Implemented stage — executed DCF with scenarios, projections, terminal value and sensitivity checks;  
Represent stage — used a three-prong approach (DCF, trading comps, precedents) and visualizations;  
Validate stage — performed checks (terminal value share, implied multiples and control premiums) to ensure model consistency.
